-- Tesla Gains After 1st U.S. Automaker IPO in 54 Years
-- Daniel Hauck
-- 2010-06-29T19:58:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/tesla-motors-shares-surge-after-first-ipo-by-a-u-s-automaker-in-54-years.html

          
          
             Tesla Motors Inc., the electric-car
company that hasn’t posted a profit, surged as much as 45
percent to $24.62 after completing the first intial public
offering of a U.S. automaker in a half century.  
 Tesla rallied even as the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index
declined 3 percent.  
